1. Enumerate the MySQL server and determine the version in use. (Format: MySQL X.X.XX)
nmap <ADDRESS> -p3306 -sV

2. During our penetration test, we found weak credentials "robin:robin". We should try these against the MySQL server. What is the email address of the customer "Otto Lang"?

mysql -u robin -probin -h <ADDRESS>
show databses;   (this shows one called customers along with some others)
use customers; (change to customers database)
select * from myTable; (the only table in customers database is myTable, this command shows all row and columns for it)

The table is quite short so it's easy to find Otto Lang's email, but filters could be used 
or commands such as "select * from <table> where <column> = "<string>";" 
